                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d120">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to
                        Generalissimo <persName type="to">Chiang Kai-shek</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="3" type="source" xml:id="d120fn3">Photostatic copy obtained from the
                        Franklin D. Roosevelt Library, Hyde Park, N. Y.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-21">August 21,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Generalissimo</hi>: I am asking Mr. Wendell Willkie
                    to make every effort to visit you in Chungking on his return to the United
                    States from Moscow.</p>
                <p>As you know, Mr. Willkie was the candidate against me in the 1940 elections and
                    as such is the titular leader of the opposition. He has given unstinted support
                    to the Government in its foreign policy and in the conduct of the war, and has
                    helped to create the excellent state of unity which exists today.</p>
                <p>I particularly want him to meet you and your good wife, for I know that much good
                    will come therefrom. I want him to realize your many and great problems and to
                    tell you something of our problems as well.</p>
                <p>I do hope that Madame Chiang will soon be able to come to the United States. Mrs.
                    Roosevelt and I eagerly await her arrival.</p>
                <p>Always sincerely,</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
